Akeeba CMS Update 1.0.5
================================================================================
# [HIGH] Hosts with PHP Safe Mode or open_basedir restrictions displayed an invalid HTTP 302 header message and couldn't download the update.

Akeeba CMS Update 1.0.4
================================================================================
~ Changed the default update preference to "Current branch or LTS release" which is the best choice for Joomla! 3.x
~ Updated .htaccess files for Apache 2.4 compatibility
~ Now using the download and update libraries in FOF

Akeeba CMS Update 1.0.3
================================================================================
! Javascript bug broke the update process

Akeeba CMS Update 1.0.2
================================================================================
! [SECURITY: High] Possibility of arbitrary file writing while an update is being extracted
~ Some servers seem to try and load the AkeebaUsagestats class twice
# [MEDIUM] CLI auto-update script doesn't work

Akeeba CMS Update 1.0.1
================================================================================
# [HIGH] References to FOF instead of F0F would cause problems on Joomla! 2.5

Akeeba CMS Update 1.0.0
================================================================================
+ Anonymous reporting of PHP, MySQL and CMS versions (opt-out through the options)
~ Even better workaround for very badly written system plugins which output Javascript without a trailing semicolon and/or newline, leading to Javascript errors. This is not a bug in our software, it's a bug in those badly written plugins and WE have to work around THEIR bad code!
# [HIGH] The component wouldn't work on Joomla! 2.5

Akeeba CMS Update 1.0.b2 (BETA)
================================================================================
# [HIGH] F0F not installed on clean installations

